well-received so far.

00:01:32.930 --> 00:01:35.555
And what I want to try and talk
about in a little bit of detail

00:01:35.555 --> 00:01:38.930
are some of the myths that I
try and dispel in the book.

00:01:38.930 --> 00:01:42.800
Usually, the first thing that
most of my friends and even

00:01:42.800 --> 00:01:44.630
my family still
ask me is actually,

00:01:44.630 --> 00:01:46.680
what do you do as
a football lawyer?

00:01:46.680 --> 00:01:49.460
So what is it that you do
that pays the bills that's

00:01:49.460 --> 00:01:51.730
cool enough to say that
you're a football lawyer

00:01:51.730 --> 00:01:54.620
and work in the
football industry doing?

00:01:54.620 --> 00:01:58.440
So very briefly,
it is as follows.

00:01:58.440 --> 00:02:02.400
On a day-to-day basis, I tend
to work with players and agents.

00:02:02.400 --> 00:02:04.850
So that is what I do.

00:02:04.850 --> 00:02:07.430
That tends, traditionally,
to be behind a computer,

00:02:07.430 --> 00:02:11.900
but very often is on
WhatsApp, is on my phone,

00:02:11.900 --> 00:02:14.810
is on voice messages that come
to me sometimes at 4 o'clock

00:02:14.810 --> 00:02:15.780
in the morning.

00:02:15.780 --> 00:02:17.420
So I'll give you one
just brief example

00:02:17.420 --> 00:02:21.020
of what happened to me the
day before transfer deadline

00:02:21.020 --> 00:02:23.720
day-- so Wednesday evening.

00:02:23.720 --> 00:02:26.840
I won't, obviously,
disclose confidential stuff.

00:02:26.840 --> 00:02:30.050
But just to give you a flavor of
what tends to happen very often

00:02:30.050 --> 00:02:32.810
is a message will come to
me from a client that may be

00:02:32.810 --> 00:02:34.280
a club or a player or an agent.

00:02:34.280 --> 00:02:37.035
Usually, it's an agent
or a club saying, right--

00:02:37.035 --> 00:02:37.785
this is happening.

00:02:37.785 --> 00:02:39.707
A deal's happening on
this particular day.

00:02:39.707 --> 00:02:41.540
We need you to just
have a little quick look

00:02:41.540 --> 00:02:43.730
through the documents,
is always what they say.

00:02:43.730 --> 00:02:49.988
And that happened actually at
1:45 AM on Thursday morning.

00:02:49.988 --> 00:02:51.530
Dan, there's a deal
that's happening.

00:02:51.530 --> 00:02:53.072
You need to get on
a train somewhere.

00:02:53.072 --> 00:02:55.670
You need to get to the
meeting for lunch time,

00:02:55.670 --> 00:02:57.470
try and conclude the
deal in the afternoon,

00:02:57.470 --> 00:02:59.220
and then hopefully
everything will be done

00:02:59.220 --> 00:03:02.630
before deadline day concludes.

00:03:02.630 --> 00:03:04.820
And that type of stuff
happens very regularly.

00:03:04.820 --> 00:03:07.280
The other cool element that
happens quite regularly

00:03:07.280 --> 00:03:13.700
is when I tend to
know information

00:03:13.700 --> 00:03:17.400
that nobody else knows,
which obviously is very cool.

00:03:17.400 --> 00:03:20.330
But I need to be extremely
careful about telling anybody

00:03:20.330 --> 00:03:22.220
this, especially
because my family are

00:03:22.220 --> 00:03:24.710
the biggest blabbermouths
of all time as well.

00:03:24.710 --> 00:03:25.490
And it happens.

00:03:25.490 --> 00:03:28.700
Because I did a Liverpool
transfer over the summer.

00:03:28.700 --> 00:03:31.880
I knew a lot of cool
stuff that was going on

00:03:31.880 --> 00:03:34.040
and couldn't tell anybody.

00:03:34.040 --> 00:03:35.990
And the brilliant
thing about it also

00:03:35.990 --> 00:03:40.670
was that he was asking me
about particular deals that

00:03:40.670 --> 00:03:42.155
were going on.

00:03:42.155 --> 00:03:46.170
And I couldn't even deny the
existence of what was going on.

00:03:46.170 --> 00:03:48.830
So for about a week and a half,
I couldn't even reply to him.

00:03:48.830 --> 00:03:52.040
So he thought I was just
being annoying, not replying

00:03:52.040 --> 00:03:55.520
to the general rumor mill
that was going on generally.

00:03:55.520 --> 00:03:57.770
But it was actually, because
one of the players that I

00:03:57.770 --> 00:04:00.650
was working with was going to be
signing a deal with Liverpool.

00:04:00.650 --> 00:04:01.850
And I couldn't even
tell my dad, obviously,

00:04:01.850 --> 00:04:03.725
which is very important,
because he obviously

00:04:03.725 --> 00:04:06.020
wants to know the gossip and
what's going on generally.

00:04:06.020 --> 00:04:08.870
But needless to say, as
soon as the deal happened,

00:04:08.870 --> 00:04:11.810
I could then tell my dad and
my rest of my family, who

00:04:11.810 --> 00:04:13.310
had no idea what was going on.

00:04:13.310 --> 00:04:15.230
But I still couldn't tell them
anything interesting about what

00:04:15.230 --> 00:04:16.449
happened in the deal,
because obviously that

00:04:16.449 --> 00:04:17.760
was confidential too.

00:04:17.760 --> 00:04:21.649
So that the type of stuff
that I tend to do is,

00:04:21.649 --> 00:04:24.275
unfortunately-- and the
glamorous side is great.

00:04:24.275 --> 00:04:26.150
You're working with so
many fantastic players

00:04:26.150 --> 00:04:27.320
with great clubs.

00:04:27.320 --> 00:04:29.060
They're spending lots of money.

00:04:29.060 --> 00:04:33.440
It is, without doubt, the
most terribly stressful hours

00:04:33.440 --> 00:04:37.130
of my life on a regular basis
when the window is cropping

00:04:37.130 --> 00:04:38.660
up or finishing or concluding.

00:04:38.660 --> 00:04:42.812
Because you're managing risk.

00:04:42.812 --> 00:04:44.270
On one sense, you
want to make sure

00:04:44.270 --> 00:04:45.860
that the deal
completes, because you

00:04:45.860 --> 00:04:48.410
don't want to be at blame if
it has anything to do with you.

00:04:48.410 --> 00:04:50.535
You are still trying to
communicate quite difficult

00:04:50.535 --> 00:04:53.930
legal concepts to your clients
to explain what the risk is

00:04:53.930 --> 00:04:55.730
of particular things happening.

00:04:55.730 --> 00:04:57.710
And at the same
time also, you're

00:04:57.710 --> 00:05:01.820
trying to make sure that you
are being proactive-- you're

00:05:01.820 --> 00:05:04.560
thinking about solutions
and things generally

00:05:04.560 --> 00:05:05.640
are going to plan.

00:05:05.640 --> 00:05:07.360
And you want to look unruffled.

00:05:07.360 --> 00:05:09.480
And looking unruffled
and feeling unruffled

00:05:09.480 --> 00:05:11.430
are two quite different
things at times.

00:05:11.430 --> 00:05:15.090
So that's just a very brief
way of a background as to what

00:05:15.090 --> 00:05:17.100
I actually do day-to-day.

00:05:17.100 --> 00:05:19.480
So about me-- we've
had the intro.

00:05:19.480 --> 00:05:22.210
This is where it all
began is the truth.

00:05:22.210 --> 00:05:28.240
So my seat was just above the
directors' box-- about there.

00:05:28.240 --> 00:05:31.520
And as you can imagine,
there's this big pole.

00:05:31.520 --> 00:05:35.700
That got in the way of the goal
basically, which is a problem.

00:05:35.700 --> 00:05:37.940
So me and my bro had
to alternate games--

00:05:37.940 --> 00:05:38.690
had to swap seats.

00:05:38.690 --> 00:05:40.773
So one of us could see the
main goal and one of us

00:05:40.773 --> 00:05:43.080
couldn't for a particular
game, which worked out well.

00:05:43.080 --> 00:05:44.495
Now, this is the old stadium.

00:05:44.495 --> 00:05:45.870
So it's now a
cantilever stadium.

00:05:45.870 --> 00:05:49.320
So it's slightly better.

00:05:49.320 --> 00:05:52.420
How did I get
involved in football?

00:05:52.420 --> 00:05:56.570
So very briefly-- what happened
in law school at university

00:05:56.570 --> 00:06:00.120
was that I asked my tutor,
literally off the cuff,

00:06:00.120 --> 00:06:02.310
can I write about
the Bosman ruling?

00:06:02.310 --> 00:06:04.470
And the Bosman ruling
was Jean-Marc Bosman,

00:06:04.470 --> 00:06:08.280
back in the day, in
1990, wasn't allowed

00:06:08.280 --> 00:06:11.790
to transfer to a new club
after the end of his contract--

00:06:11.790 --> 00:06:13.410
after it even expired.

00:06:13.410 --> 00:06:15.480
And that started a
very big landmark case

00:06:15.480 --> 00:06:18.210
which, five years
later, actually resulted

00:06:18.210 --> 00:06:20.340
in what's called the
free movement of players

00:06:20.340 --> 00:06:21.390
across Europe.

00:06:21.390 --> 00:06:24.540
Which meant that, after a
player's contract had finished,

00:06:24.540 --> 00:06:26.460
they could move on
a free transfer.

00:06:26.460 --> 00:06:29.100
And the selling club
didn't have to demand

00:06:29.100 --> 00:06:30.990
and couldn't demand
a transfer fee.

00:06:30.990 --> 00:06:32.490
So I thought, what
a brilliant thing

00:06:32.490 --> 00:06:35.430
to possibly, in third
year uni, write about,

00:06:35.430 --> 00:06:38.700
which was the Bosman ruling,
the transfer system changing,

00:06:38.700 --> 00:06:39.990
and how things would work.

00:06:39.990 --> 00:06:42.390
And they let me write about
it, which was even better.

00:06:42.390 --> 00:06:44.610
After that, I
actually just tried

00:06:44.610 --> 00:06:47.820
to persuade my dad for me to
spend an extra year at uni,

00:06:47.820 --> 00:06:50.610
which he was happy for me to do
if I did something interesting.

00:06:50.610 --> 00:06:53.938
I did a masters in football
broadcasting rights.

00:06:53.938 --> 00:06:55.980
It didn't sound as
interesting because, actually,

00:06:55.980 --> 00:06:58.147
underpinning it was competition
law, which obviously

00:06:58.147 --> 00:07:00.420
is not quite as sexy
as football law,

00:07:00.420 --> 00:07:03.150
but at the same time meant
that I could spend the best

00:07:03.150 --> 00:07:06.780
part of about nine or 10 months
writing about how broadcasting

00:07:06.780 --> 00:07:09.930
rights are sold across
Europe, which is cool.

00:07:09.930 --> 00:07:11.577
And it meant that
I could get out

00:07:11.577 --> 00:07:13.410
of the real world for
one more year before I

00:07:13.410 --> 00:07:15.990
had to start working.

00:07:15.990 --> 00:07:19.028
As a result of that
masters degree,

00:07:19.028 --> 00:07:20.820
I had a little bit of
spare time at the end

00:07:20.820 --> 00:07:22.080
of the year, which
actually meant

00:07:22.080 --> 00:07:23.490
that my tutor said
to me, instead

00:07:23.490 --> 00:07:25.380
of actually just
slacking off, why did you

00:07:25.380 --> 00:07:27.840
write in a couple of law
journals about the things

00:07:27.840 --> 00:07:29.285
that you've written about.

00:07:29.285 --> 00:07:31.410
Great-- OK, I could do
that-- didn't think anything

00:07:31.410 --> 00:07:31.980
would happen.

00:07:31.980 --> 00:07:34.260
But in a fantastic
way, they were

00:07:34.260 --> 00:07:37.020
happy to publish something about
the football industry, which

00:07:37.020 --> 00:07:39.927
was broadcasting rights
and about club ownership.

00:07:39.927 --> 00:07:41.760
"The Entertainment Law
Review," at the time,

00:07:41.760 --> 00:07:45.225
published those two articles
in a few months spells.

00:07:45.225 --> 00:07:47.100
But what I actually
realized afterwards that,

00:07:47.100 --> 00:07:49.290
as well is it was
great for my ego--

00:07:49.290 --> 00:07:52.530
fantastic getting in "The
Entertainment Sports Journal,"

00:07:52.530 --> 00:07:57.060
great to have the publicity,
fantastic to show a few people

00:07:57.060 --> 00:07:58.195
and have it on my CV--

00:07:58.195 --> 00:08:00.570
the truth was-- I don't mean
to say it badly against "The

00:08:00.570 --> 00:08:03.060
Entertainment Law Review"--
maybe only about eight people

00:08:03.060 --> 00:08:04.270
read it.

00:08:04.270 --> 00:08:05.700
It's the truth.

00:08:05.700 --> 00:08:09.342
And you'll soon find out
from a little bit of the talk

00:08:09.342 --> 00:08:10.800
that I give in a
little bit of time

00:08:10.800 --> 00:08:13.620
is, what I actually realized,
as much as it was really

00:08:13.620 --> 00:08:16.650
good for the ego, because
no one was reading it,

00:08:16.650 --> 00:08:20.167
I actually needed to increase
my profile to a degree.

00:08:20.167 --> 00:08:21.750
And the way that I
actually did that--

00:08:21.750 --> 00:08:24.420
I'd met my wife Holly in 2007.

00:08:24.420 --> 00:08:28.320
And quite quickly, we
talked about all the stuff

00:08:28.320 --> 00:08:30.581
that I could do in my job
and wanted to do in my job.

00:08:30.581 --> 00:08:32.789
She actually then said to
me, well, hold on a second.

00:08:32.789 --> 00:08:35.520
Why are you writing
5,000 or 6,000 words

00:08:35.520 --> 00:08:37.260
for an entertainment
law journal when

00:08:37.260 --> 00:08:39.900
you could be writing 500
words on your own blog,

00:08:39.900 --> 00:08:42.750
free, that everybody could
be able to then access

00:08:42.750 --> 00:08:44.330
and read accordingly.

00:08:44.330 --> 00:08:45.913
And I actually
thought, you know what?

00:08:45.913 --> 00:08:47.550
It's actually a
pretty good idea.

00:08:47.550 --> 00:08:51.270
And so what I ended
up doing was not

00:08:51.270 --> 00:08:53.370
necessary not writing
in law journals

00:08:53.370 --> 00:08:55.860
overall but,
ultimately, deciding

00:08:55.860 --> 00:08:58.470
to start my own website,
which is DanielGeey.com,

00:08:58.470 --> 00:09:03.750
and then effectively
start writing small pieces

00:09:03.750 --> 00:09:06.840
about trying to demystify the
football industry to a degree,

00:09:06.840 --> 00:09:08.430
even though actually,
at the time,

00:09:08.430 --> 00:09:11.220
I wasn't doing a huge
amount of work in football.

00:09:11.220 --> 00:09:12.220
I was doing small bits.

00:09:12.220 --> 00:09:14.790
It was hopefully increasing in
the type of work I was doing.

00:09:14.790 --> 00:09:17.610
But I wasn't doing huge
amounts at that time.

00:09:17.610 --> 00:09:20.340
And it came,
actually, at a very--

00:09:20.340 --> 00:09:23.400
fruitful is the wrong word--
but a really interesting time

00:09:23.400 --> 00:09:24.780
in the football industry.

00:09:24.780 --> 00:09:26.670
There was financial
fair play, which

00:09:26.670 --> 00:09:27.990
I'll talk about in some detail.

00:09:27.990 --> 00:09:29.760
There was third-party
ownership, which

00:09:29.760 --> 00:09:31.650
was a big thing at the time.

00:09:31.650 --> 00:09:35.080
Luis Suarez came to the country.

00:09:35.080 --> 00:09:37.440
And obviously, he
had a lot of issues

00:09:37.440 --> 00:09:41.280
with racism, with
biting, with suspensions.

00:09:41.280 --> 00:09:44.580
John Terry matter
came up as well.

00:09:44.580 --> 00:09:46.750
And Nicolas Anelka
happened at the same time.

00:09:46.750 --> 00:09:49.230
So what was actually happening--
which is quite cool--

00:09:49.230 --> 00:09:54.030
is that there were lots of
cases and lots of issues that

00:09:54.030 --> 00:09:54.690
the public--

00:09:54.690 --> 00:09:57.760
the wide fans-- really
wanted to know about.

00:09:57.760 --> 00:10:00.180
And what I had-- a little
bit more time before kids

00:10:00.180 --> 00:10:03.530
and marriage-- was to be
able to read these cases,

00:10:03.530 --> 00:10:06.950
try and explain what they
meant for the average fan,

00:10:06.950 --> 00:10:08.660
and try and get beyond the--

00:10:08.660 --> 00:10:12.710
Luis Suarez is a racist
or it's a three match

00:10:12.710 --> 00:10:16.100
ban for fouling
somebody or, actually,

00:10:16.100 --> 00:10:18.800
if you look at the detail of a
particular case, it means that

00:10:18.800 --> 00:10:20.020
or it means this.

00:10:20.020 --> 00:10:22.170
And what I developed--

00:10:22.170 --> 00:10:25.880
which was great-- was quite a
strong follower base on Twitter

00:10:25.880 --> 00:10:29.300
as well, which was a great
amplifier of my blogs,

00:10:29.300 --> 00:10:32.900
to be able to then put
forward easily-accessible,

00:10:32.900 --> 00:10:36.050
easily-digestible 500,
600, 700-word blogs

00:10:36.050 --> 00:10:37.990
that people were interested in.

00:10:37.990 --> 00:10:39.740
And then what happened
as a result of that

00:10:39.740 --> 00:10:41.810
was that journalists--

00:10:41.810 --> 00:10:44.330
Sky Sports-- all the
types of broadcast media--

00:10:44.330 --> 00:10:48.320
were then interested in having
me on their shows really,

00:10:48.320 --> 00:10:49.730
which was great.

00:10:49.730 --> 00:10:54.530
And that in itself
then drove the profile

00:10:54.530 --> 00:10:57.080
that I was able to drive
for myself and my firm.

00:10:57.080 --> 00:11:01.220
I was able then to refine
my message that I wanted

00:11:01.220 --> 00:11:02.660
to get across to people--

00:11:02.660 --> 00:11:05.930
and in turn, led
me then to that,

00:11:05.930 --> 00:11:07.790
which was from blog to book.

00:11:07.790 --> 00:11:10.490
So I used to give a lot
of comments and commentary

00:11:10.490 --> 00:11:12.680
to people in the
football industry.

00:11:12.680 --> 00:11:14.527
Someone-- a
journalist-- said, why

00:11:14.527 --> 00:11:16.610
don't you think about
writing a book on the topic?

00:11:16.610 --> 00:11:17.750
And I said, oh, great idea.

00:11:17.750 --> 00:11:19.167
I don't think
anyone will actually

00:11:19.167 --> 00:11:20.870
think and be interested in it.

00:11:20.870 --> 00:11:23.810
He introduced me to an
agent, David Luxton,

00:11:23.810 --> 00:11:26.690
who is bizarrely my agent,
which is quite strange to say,

