of the things he always
wanted to do was go to space.

00:48:25.080 --> 00:48:26.790
So Sunderland
apparently put a clause

00:48:26.790 --> 00:48:29.940
in saying, during
your time at our club,

00:48:29.940 --> 00:48:33.870
you are prohibited
from going into space.

00:48:33.870 --> 00:48:36.578
And there was another one which
is from a Liverpool player--

00:48:36.578 --> 00:48:37.370
next level player--

00:48:37.370 --> 00:48:41.660
Stig Inge Bjornebye, who was
a Norwegian international.

00:48:41.660 --> 00:48:44.340
His father was, I
think, an Olympic skier.

00:48:44.340 --> 00:48:46.290
And Liverpool ensured
that there was

00:48:46.290 --> 00:48:48.600
a clause in which said he
couldn't ski during the time

00:48:48.600 --> 00:48:52.020
that he was a Liverpool player,
for obvious reasons really.

00:48:52.020 --> 00:48:53.650
And that is quite
a standard clause,

00:48:53.650 --> 00:48:56.025
that you can't do anything
hazardous, for obvious reasons

00:48:56.025 --> 00:48:57.773
that you would
probably hurt yourself.

00:48:57.773 --> 00:48:59.940
AUDIENCE: Just a quick
question about the boot stuff

00:48:59.940 --> 00:49:00.982
that you put up as well--

00:49:00.982 --> 00:49:02.440
I've got a good
friend actually who

00:49:02.440 --> 00:49:03.790
works for one of the big two.

00:49:03.790 --> 00:49:07.945
And he was saying-- about one of
the biggest challenges he cites

00:49:07.945 --> 00:49:09.570
with working with
some of the players--

00:49:09.570 --> 00:49:12.630
he looks after five Premier
League clubs, I think--

00:49:12.630 --> 00:49:14.790
is their egos and
their personalities.

00:49:14.790 --> 00:49:16.890
And they all want
things for free,

00:49:16.890 --> 00:49:19.440
even though they
earn mega money.

00:49:19.440 --> 00:49:23.220
So I suppose, my question
is around expectations.

00:49:23.220 --> 00:49:25.820
How do you deal with
expectations with players

00:49:25.820 --> 00:49:27.610
and with big egos?

00:49:27.610 --> 00:49:29.840
Well, not everyone's
got big egos--

00:49:29.840 --> 00:49:31.430
and brushing everybody.

00:49:31.430 --> 00:49:34.520
But yeah-- how do you deal
with those expectations

00:49:34.520 --> 00:49:37.170
of players and big players?

00:49:37.170 --> 00:49:38.790
DANIEL GEEY: Are
you talking about--

00:49:38.790 --> 00:49:40.240
in terms of boot deals?--
or just generally?

00:49:40.240 --> 00:49:41.670
AUDIENCE: Just generally-- yeah.

00:49:41.670 --> 00:49:43.580
I suppose, it's quite
difficult to manage--

00:49:43.580 --> 00:49:45.180
yeah.

00:49:45.180 --> 00:49:47.580
DANIEL GEEY: Simple
truth is that,

00:49:47.580 --> 00:49:50.580
of the players that I have
close relationships with--

00:49:50.580 --> 00:49:52.470
and literally, it's hilarious.

00:49:52.470 --> 00:49:52.970
I'm cool.

00:49:52.970 --> 00:49:55.470
As a football fan, they'll just
WhatsApp you and say, hello.

00:49:55.470 --> 00:49:57.480
And literally, I'm giving
book recommendations

00:49:57.480 --> 00:50:02.850
to one player, who's
interested in just expanding

00:50:02.850 --> 00:50:04.987
his repertoire of
reading at the moment,

00:50:04.987 --> 00:50:06.570
because they have
loads of away trips.

00:50:06.570 --> 00:50:09.780
And he's got lots of
time on his hands.

00:50:09.780 --> 00:50:13.898
But the majority of
players that I end up

00:50:13.898 --> 00:50:15.690
having good relationships
with are the guys

00:50:15.690 --> 00:50:17.760
that want to know the detail--

00:50:17.760 --> 00:50:18.930
is the truth.

00:50:18.930 --> 00:50:21.642
And usually, in my
experience, the players

00:50:21.642 --> 00:50:23.850
that want to know the detail
are the most switched on

00:50:23.850 --> 00:50:27.210
to understand the
way things work.

00:50:27.210 --> 00:50:29.370
The players that maybe
don't are the ones

00:50:29.370 --> 00:50:31.148
that I'll be like,
just leave it.

00:50:31.148 --> 00:50:32.190
And let the lawyer do it.

00:50:32.190 --> 00:50:33.210
Let the accountant do it.

00:50:33.210 --> 00:50:34.710
Let the agent do
it-- however it is.

00:50:34.710 --> 00:50:36.030
That's absolutely fine too.

00:50:36.030 --> 00:50:39.317
But usually-- I don't like
to call it prima dona status

00:50:39.317 --> 00:50:41.900
actually, because maybe they're
not as educated as they need--

00:50:41.900 --> 00:50:45.720
as the team around them need
to give them to make sure they

00:50:45.720 --> 00:50:49.350
understand what they need to be
doing on a daily basis to get

00:50:49.350 --> 00:50:49.950
by--

00:50:49.950 --> 00:50:51.122
is the truth.

00:50:51.122 --> 00:50:52.830
And what I try and do
a lot of the time--

00:50:52.830 --> 00:50:54.663
just to flip it onto
the positive-- is that,

00:50:54.663 --> 00:50:55.880
every time a new player--

00:50:55.880 --> 00:50:57.630
even if it's a young
player-- especially--

00:50:57.630 --> 00:50:59.172
comes into the office
to say, hello--

00:50:59.172 --> 00:51:00.570
or helping them with the deal--

00:51:00.570 --> 00:51:01.537
my idea is, like, look.

00:51:01.537 --> 00:51:03.870
Just give me 1/2 an hour with
the agents and the player.

00:51:03.870 --> 00:51:06.015
I just want to talk you
through particular things

00:51:06.015 --> 00:51:08.390
that I think are going to be
important for the next deal,

00:51:08.390 --> 00:51:10.745
for the next endorsement
deal you're signing.

00:51:10.745 --> 00:51:12.870
Think about what you're
doing on Twitter, or Insta,

00:51:12.870 --> 00:51:16.410
or Snap or Tinder--

00:51:16.410 --> 00:51:17.010
literally.

00:51:17.010 --> 00:51:20.880
Because everybody has a phone.

00:51:20.880 --> 00:51:22.890
Everybody has a video.

00:51:22.890 --> 00:51:26.160
Everybody wants to catch
someone out doing something

00:51:26.160 --> 00:51:27.808
they shouldn't do who's famous.

00:51:27.808 --> 00:51:29.600
That's the truth,
unfortunately, that we're

00:51:29.600 --> 00:51:30.900
living in at the moment.

00:51:30.900 --> 00:51:33.450
Players 20 years ago were
in, in a way, a much more

00:51:33.450 --> 00:51:34.410
privileged position.

00:51:34.410 --> 00:51:36.493
They could probably get
away with a lot more stuff

00:51:36.493 --> 00:51:37.930
that players can't do now.

00:51:37.930 --> 00:51:39.740
So that's almost
the point, which is,

00:51:39.740 --> 00:51:42.060
I'm trying just
to flip and pivot

00:51:42.060 --> 00:51:45.075
the narrative, which is,
get players better educated

00:51:45.075 --> 00:51:46.450
as to what they
need to be doing,

00:51:46.450 --> 00:51:48.328
so they can make more
informed decisions.

00:51:48.328 --> 00:51:49.870
Always, players will
do things wrong.

00:51:49.870 --> 00:51:53.620
They're as fallible as us.

00:51:53.620 --> 00:51:55.620
I think people just like
a bit of schadenfreude,

00:51:55.620 --> 00:51:57.703
where a famous person who's
earning a lot of money

00:51:57.703 --> 00:52:00.510
does something stupid.

00:52:00.510 --> 00:52:02.820
AUDIENCE: Just
wondering how you manage

00:52:02.820 --> 00:52:07.320
your clients' expectations when
you're dealing with someone

00:52:07.320 --> 00:52:10.740
who-- so for example, a
player that is injury prone--

00:52:10.740 --> 00:52:13.830
and you're going to see that
in their boot sponsorship deals

00:52:13.830 --> 00:52:15.480
and in their appearances.

00:52:15.480 --> 00:52:19.292
A lot of that is tied to
their appearances and--

00:52:19.292 --> 00:52:20.250
how you deal with that.

00:52:23.100 --> 00:52:26.160
DANIEL GEEY: It's
a really good one.

00:52:26.160 --> 00:52:29.370
It depends how you classify
injury-prone-- is the truth.

00:52:29.370 --> 00:52:31.140
Now, either you do
one of two things.

00:52:31.140 --> 00:52:34.320
As an agent, you can strategize
beforehand to say, right.

00:52:34.320 --> 00:52:37.590
We've got three boot deal
offerings on the table.

00:52:37.590 --> 00:52:41.010
The retainer amount
is this amount

00:52:41.010 --> 00:52:42.840
for this particular
manufacturer.

00:52:42.840 --> 00:52:45.060
We think an estimate that--
because over last three

00:52:45.060 --> 00:52:48.090
seasons, the players
played 25 games per season,

00:52:48.090 --> 00:52:51.330
because either injuries
or form-- whatever it is.

00:52:51.330 --> 00:52:54.270
We need to try and get to
this number with this amount

00:52:54.270 --> 00:52:56.520
of appearances that we think
we can get for the player

00:52:56.520 --> 00:52:57.820
every season.

00:52:57.820 --> 00:52:59.910
So in a way, it's a
reverse engineering

00:52:59.910 --> 00:53:03.600
of the contractual
matrix, in order

00:53:03.600 --> 00:53:07.260
to make sure that you can
get the player over the line,

00:53:07.260 --> 00:53:09.213
saying, this is the
amount that you may earn.

00:53:09.213 --> 00:53:11.130
But you're probably going
to earn this amount,

00:53:11.130 --> 00:53:13.297
because of the amount of
games you're going to play.

00:53:13.297 --> 00:53:15.390
And ultimately, what
can sometimes happen--

00:53:15.390 --> 00:53:17.740
which can help-- is on
the appearance side,

00:53:17.740 --> 00:53:19.360
which I didn't quite touch on.

00:53:19.360 --> 00:53:21.270
If you're savvy enough,
what you can actually

00:53:21.270 --> 00:53:24.000
say to the boot
manufacturer is, we're

00:53:24.000 --> 00:53:25.620
only going to
classify appearance

00:53:25.620 --> 00:53:28.950
as particular competitions.

00:53:28.950 --> 00:53:30.630
Because if you're
an elite athlete--

00:53:30.630 --> 00:53:33.570
elite footballer--
you're probably

00:53:33.570 --> 00:53:36.580
less likely to play in
FA Cup and League Cup

00:53:36.580 --> 00:53:39.240
and more likely to play in
Champions League and Premier

00:53:39.240 --> 00:53:40.230
League.

00:53:40.230 --> 00:53:45.840
So what you would try and do,
if you're the agent acting

00:53:45.840 --> 00:53:46.890
for elite player--

00:53:46.890 --> 00:53:52.710
you'd try and exclude the cup
competitions to try and ensure

00:53:52.710 --> 00:53:56.513
that, if appearance is
defined as 80% of those games,

00:53:56.513 --> 00:53:58.680
you're more likely to about
to hit those benchmarks.

00:53:58.680 --> 00:54:01.430
[APPLAUSE]

